{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Remove \u201cpositive action for recruitment and promotion\u201d from the Equality Act",
        "additional_details": "I believe that this is not positive but unethical and discriminatory. A law supposed to prevent discrimination encourages it, particularly when it comes to employment. Nobody should be at an advantage and nobody should be at a disadvantage due to their ethnicity or any other factor they have no control over. I want the positive action exemption for recruitment and promotion to be removed from the Equality Act.",
        "background": "Under the Equality Act, an employer can use \"positive action\" to promote or recruit a candidate from a certain group with a protected characteristic deemed to be under-represented in the work force if they are considered \"as qualified as\" another candidate who isn't from that group. ",
